<HEAD>Smoker Arrested After Scuffle on Trans-Atlantic Flight</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WINNIPEG, Manitoba (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Danish man tussled with the crew of
a trans-Atlantic flight, tried to open the airplane's door, and
threw a drink in the pilot's face after he was caught smoking,
police said.
   Oly Svane Thestrup, 41, of Copenhagen, was charged in a Winnipeg
court Wednesday.
   The incident happened Tuesday on a British Airways flight from
London to Los Angeles after a passenger set off a smoke detector in
a washroom on the Boeing 747, police said.
   He struggled with the crew, tried to open a door on the plane,
and threw a drink in the pilot's face, they said.
   The man was restrained but managed to free himself.
   The pilot landed at Winnipeg International Airport, where the
plane was met by police.
