<HEAD>Reagan, Dukakis To Visit Governors' Meeting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan and Democratic presidential
nominee Michael Dukakis plan to visit the National Governors'
Association annual meeting on successive days next month, a
spokeswoman for Ohio Gov. Richard Celeste said.
   The association will conduct its 80th annual meeting Aug. 7-9 in
Cincinnati.
   Reagan is to address the governors on Aug. 8 at the Cincinnati
Convention Center, said Heidi Findley, Celeste's deputy press
secretary.
   Dukakis, the governor of Massachusetts, plans to attend either a
closing session of the governors' meeting on Aug. 9 or a meeting
that day in Cincinnati of the Democratic Governors' Association,
Ms. Findley said.
   Vice President George Bush, the assured Republican nominee for
president, has given no indication whether he plans to attend the
governors' meeting, Ms. Findley said.
