<1ST_LINE>r i PM-India-PoliceStrike     07-28 0221</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-India-Police Strike,0225</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Policemen Strike, Three Die in Gujarat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rioters fatally stabbed three people in
the western state of Gujarat, where a police strike entered its
fourth day today and prompted officials to call out the army, the
Press Trust of India reported.
   The stabbings occurred Wednesday night in Godhra, 465 miles
southwest of New Delhi, the news agency said. The identities of the
victims and the motive behind their slayings were not immediately
known.
   The strike by state police was called after the government on
Sunday ordered the arrest of union leaders who were demanding
higher wages and better benefits. Officials accused the leaders of
inciting a police rebellion.
   The policemen walked off the job Monday in Ahmedabad, an
industrial city 18 miles south of Gandhinagar, the state capital.
The strike later spread all over the state and units of the federal
reserve police and other paramilitary forces were ordered to take
up routine police duties.
   Policemen in 138 out of the state's 426 police stations joined
in the strike, the sixth by Gujarat police in nine years, the
government said.
   The policemen are asking for a monthly $75 wage hike. A
constable earns about $142 a month.
   At least 83 policemen have so far been dismissed and 23 arrested
on charges of indiscipline.
</TEXT>
