<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Producer David L. Wolper, who staged the
dazzling closing ceremonies at the 1984 Summer Olympic Games in Los
Angeles, has signed an exclusive contract with Warner Bros. Inc.
   Wolper's contract runs until 1995 and extends the association
he's had with the studio since selling his production company to
Warner in 1976. The financial terms weren't disclosed.
   During his 12 years at Warner, Wolper has produced 80 hours of
miniseries, among them 26 hours of ``Roots,'' 24 hours of ``North
and South,'' and 10 hours of ``The Thorn Birds.''
   Wolper's forthcoming film,``Imagine: John Lennon,'' will be
released in October.
