<HEAD>Oman Hotel Makes World's Longest Shish Kebab</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUSCAT, Oman (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Muscat hotel has won the record for making
the world's longest shish kebab, the hotel claimed Thursday.
   The Ruwi Novotel cooked a 459-foot kebab, a feat now officially
recognized by the Guinness Book of Records, according to hotel
executives.
   Hotel manager Georges Sirguey, who thought up the idea of
cooking the longest ``Turkish-Moghulai'' kebab, said: ``We are
absolutely thrilled.''
   Sirguey said many people laughed when they heard about what his
hotel was doing. ``Well, it has been worth the effort. It was a
great team event. We feel very proud that the Guinness Book of
Records has recognized it,'' he said.
   The 330-pound kebab was cooked over 3,960 pounds of charcoal on
a giant barbecue.
