<HEAD>10 Downing St. To Be Remodeled</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The interior of 10 Downing St., the office and
residence of British prime ministers since 1732, will be remodeled
starting next week.
   Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher's press office said Wednesday
the building will undergo its first major remodeling in 17 years.
   British taxpayers will pick up the $515,000 tab.
   Most public areas of the facility _ including the entrance hall,
Cabinet anteroom, Mrs. Thatcher's study and the dining rooms _ will
be redecorated.
   No work is planned on the Cabinet room or the private apartment
at the top of the building where Mrs. Thatcher and her husband
Denis live.
   Mrs. Thatcher has helped choose the colors of the new carpets
and curtains to be installed. The work is expected to be completed
in mid-September.
