<HEAD>Couple Married 62 Years Die Within an Hour of Each Other</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA FE, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A couple who met in the 1920s and were
married for 62 years died of heart failure within an hour of each
other.
   ``He adored her from the first time he laid eyes on her, right
up to the last time he laid eyes on her,'' said Betty Ann Rose, the
daughter of Benjamin and Ruth Lippsett, who died Tuesday at 86.
   ``It's listed as heart failure, but that is not what they died
from,'' Rose said. ``He stayed until he knew she was gone and
didn't need him anymore. That's the way they wanted it.''
   Mrs. Lippsett died while nurses attended to her in Rose's house.
   ``We told Dad,'' Rose said. ``He saw her, laid down, cried some
tears and within the hour he stopped breathing.''
   Lippsett, 89, was a letter carrier.
   They are survived by Rose, a son, nine grandchildren and seven
great-grandchildren.
</TEXT>
