<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--StrandedDancers     07-28 0170</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Stranded Dancers,0173</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Donations Allow British Dancers To Fly Home</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Local residents donated $3,600 to four British
dancers who could not afford to fly home because they were
underpaid by a nightclub, their lawyer's office said Thursday.
   Keiji Shishioka of the Muramatsu-Hijii law office identified the
dancers as Colette Zacca of London, Kate Allegaert of Essex, Dawn
Sheridan Young of the Isle of Wight and Dawn Elaine Leach of Kent.
   Shishioka said the women began working in April at a nightclub
in Sapporo, northern Japan under a contract stipulating each would
receive $1,000 a month plus room and board and their flight
expenses to Britain.
   But each received only $150 after working for about two months,
he said.
   Shishioka said a court ruled June 23 the club must give the
women their back wages but the dancers were unable to collect from
the nightclub.
   The women received the donations from residents who read
newspaper accounts about their troubles. The dancers will leave for
home on Saturday.
</TEXT>
