   Eva Gabor says trying to fit in with the
boys at work is a no-no, dah-ling.
   ``When a woman goes into an office and says to a guy, `I'm as
good as you or any man,' she begins to believe it. And she becomes
like a man,'' the Hungarian-born actress said Wednesday.
   Gabor chairs the board of Eva Gabor International, a Los Angeles
wig manufacturer that sells 2 million pieces annually. She says her
company has offices in Los Angeles, Hong Kong and West Germany, and
employs 4,000 people with two factories in China and one in Korea.
   She says she doesn't mind if the public thinks of her as an
actress and not a businesswoman.
   ``That's good, because I'm female, and I intend to stay that
way. I don't want to be treated like one of the guys,'' she said.
