   Donald Trump, whose $30 million yacht was
responsible for stranding 21 angry daycampers on shore, has made
amends by inviting the group aboard for a picnic.
   The campers, girls aged 10 and 11, had planned an afternoon
cruise aboard a private schooner Tuesday. But when they arrived at
the East River, they found the 282-foot Trump Princess docked,
leaving no room for the schooner.
   The campers departed _ ``not liking Mr. Trump too much,''
according to counselor Jennifer Goren.
   Trump, who said he was unaware of the girls' plight, said they
will each receive a souvenir at the picnic.
   Miss Goren was much happier.
   ``This is what I call justice,'' she said. ``Mr. Trump is really
a cool guy.''
