<HEAD>Newspaper Says Revolutionary Guards Minister Jailed
^With AM-Gulf Rdp, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iran's Revolutionary Guards minister,
Mohsen Rafiq- Doust, has been in a Tehran prison for the past three
weeks, the Beirut newspaper Ad-Diyar reported Thursday.
   The paper, based in Christian east Beirut, said the order for
his arrest was issued by Hashemi Rafsanjani, the powerful speaker
