<HEAD>Smoker Sentenced To 90 Days for Scuffle on Trans-Atlantic Flight</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WINNIPEG, Manitoba (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Danish actor who caused a
disturbance on a trans-Atlantic flight after sneaking a smoke in
the washroom pleaded guilty to a charge of mischief Thursday and
was sentenced to 90 days in jail.
   Ole Svane Thestrup, 41, of Copenhagen was on a British Airways
flight from London to Los Angeles this week when he set off the
smoke alarm in the washroom of a Boeing 747.
   Defense lawyer Mark O'Neill said the sentence will not be
appealed.
   The crown prosecutor did not proceed with charges of endangering
an aircraft and assaulting a peace officer.
   Police said earlier that Thestrup tussled with the crew, tried
to open the airplane's door, and threw a drink in the pilot's face
after he was caught smoking during the flight Tuesday.
   The pilot made an unscheduled landing in Winnipeg, where
Thestrup was handed over to police.
