<1ST_LINE>r f BC-DelWebb     07-28 0162</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Del Webb,0168</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Real Estate Company Says It Won't Respond to Buyout Offer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Del Webb Co. said it had received a $161
million buyout offer from a Los Angeles partnership but would allow
the bid to expire without a response.
   Webb, developer of the Sun City retirement communities in
Arizona, disclosed Wednesday it had received an offer from ESA
Associates for $17.50 a share for Webb's 9.2 million outstanding
shares, the company said.
   Webb stock, which has been trading in the $13- to $15-a-share
range, closed at $14.75 in New York Stock Exchange composite
trading Wednesday, down 50 cents from Tuesday.
   Terms of the offer set a Wednesday evening expiration time and
Webb did not plan to respond, said company spokesman Ernie East. He
said Webb had not satisfied itself ESA could provide financing.
   ESA is a partnership of Century City attorney Sandy Hillsberg
and developer Robert Blake. Neither responded to an afternoon
telephone request for comment.
</TEXT>
