<FILEID>AP-NR-07-28-88 1109EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-AlleghenyInternational     07-28 0156</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Allegheny International,0162</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Allegheny International Reports Loss</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Allegheny International Inc. says it lost
$15.3 million during the company's third quarter, compared to a
loss of $29.4 million in the same period a year ago.
   The Pittsburgh-based consumer products manufacturer said
Wednesday its third-quarter loss came on sales of $233.9 million,
up from its third-quarter 1987 sales of $229.8 million.
   The company attributed the latest loss in part to the
consolidation of its Sunbeam Appliance and Oster divisions,
announced in June.
   Allegheny International also cited its reorganization under
Chapter 11 of federal bankruptcy laws and its proxy fight for
control of the company's board of directors as reasons for the
latest shortfall.
   For the first nine months of fiscal 1988, Allegheny
International reported a loss of $12.6 million on sales of $744.9
million. That compared to a loss of $233.6 million on sales of
$721.6 million during the same period of fiscal 1987.
</TEXT>
