<2ND_LINE>BC-Global Executive,0205</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Global: Former Executive Misappropriated $75,000 in Company Assets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Global Natural Resources Inc. said a former
executive who committed suicide last month misappropriated $75,000
in company assets for his own use.
   Company officials said in a Securities and Exchange Commission
filing Wednesday that John R. Dempsey, former chief executive and
president, used Global money and equipment to build two barns, a
portable building and several ranch gates on his ranch near
Brenham, Texas.
   Dempsey also may have received a payment of $28,000 in
connection with the purchase by Global of some North Dakota oil and
gas properties, according to the filing.
   The filing said that if the company is unable to reach a
settlement with Dempsey's estate, it would bring civil charges to
try to recover the money.
   Dempsey, 53, quit his $281,599-a-year job in May. He fatally
shot himself June 20, 10 days after Global concluded an
investigation of his activities, according to the SEC document.
   Global will not be financially affected by Dempsey's actions,
the oil and natural gas company said in the filing, because it has
insurance. But Global still wants to recover what it can from
Dempsey's estate.
</TEXT>
