<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street Noon,0393</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market was mostly mixed today in dull
trading as investors awaited a clearer indication on the direction
of interest rates.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 11.02 at 2,064.72
at midday.
   Gainers slightly outnumbered losers in the overall tally of New
York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 607 issues up, 581 down and
539 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 77.50 million shares as of noon
on Wall Street.
   The Dow firmed on the opening, then flirted with negative
territory before heading higher. Market watchers cautioned,
however, that any spike upward is likely to be temporary.
   Analysts noted that investors' key focus is interest rates.
``The market seems to be suffering from interest-rate paranoia,''
one trader said.
   Concern that rates might be moving upward heightened on
Wednesday when the goverment reported that inflation rose more than
4 percent in the last quarter.
   ``The market can't mount any kind of sustainable move if you
have rates going against you,'' noted Larry Wachtel, first vice
president at Prudential-Bache Securities Inc.
   He said the bond market has to stabilize on a longer term basis
before money pours back into stocks. But the credit market headed
lower again today after the Commerce Department reported that
Americans' personal incomes rose 0.7 percent while consumer
spending jumped 1.0 percent during June.
   Analysts are likely view the big rise in spending as
inflationary because it places a strain on U.S. manufacturers who
are fighting to lower the trade deficit.
   As bond prices move lower, rising yields have been attracting
funds that normally would have been earmarked for equities.
   Among actively traded Big Board issues, Interco soared 8[ at
67{. The company received a $64-a-share buyout offer from City
Capital Associates.
   York International fell 1[ to 57[. SnyderGeneral withdrew its
$61-a-share bid for the company because of antitrust concerns.
   Elsewhere, Digital Equipment rose 1\ to 103{. The market was
unenthused on Wednesday when the company reported
better-than-expected earnings. Polaroid was up 1[ at 43], and Exxon
rose | at 46\.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks edged
up 0.59 to 149.33. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was off 0.13 at 302.72.
