<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
142,941 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
156,536, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
when 142,090 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
