compared with 88,055 a week ago and 72,305 in the same week in 1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 66,190,
compared with last week's 68,481 and last year's 69,785.
   Canadian automakers were to build 9,155 cars this week, up from
5,444 a week ago and from last year's 7,727.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 11,934,
compared with 5,488 a week ago and 6,652 in the same week last
year.
