<1ST_LINE>r f BC-AMI-Heidelberg     07-28 0157</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-AMI-Heidelberg,0164</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>AM International Plans to Sell Printing Press Group to German
Company</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   AM International Inc. says it will sell its
Harris Graphics web printing press group to West Germany's
Heidelberger Druckmaschinen AG in a deal valued at $300 million.
   The offer from Heidelberg, as the printing-equipment firm is
generally known, tops a $256 million offer made in June by Komori
Printing Machinery Co. of Tokyo as well as a $203 million bid by
Komori for just the European operations of the Harris group.
   Under the definitive agreement announced Wednesday by
Chicago-based AM International, Heidelberg will assume $52 million
in subordinated debt.
   AM said that after various expenses it expects to receive more
than $230 million in sale proceeds and that it will use that cash
to reduce debt.
   AM, a $1.2 billion graphics company, bought Harris Graphics
Corp. two years ago for $246 million in cash and assumed $117
million in debt.
</TEXT>
